---
import UsePage from '../../components/UsePage.astro';
---

<UsePage
  title="QR Code with Logo — Free Generator, No Watermark | QRMint"
  description="Add your logo to a QR code free. Upload PNG, JPG, or SVG, pick brand colors, and download print-ready files. No watermark, no sign-up, codes never expire."
  heading="QR Code Generator with Logo"
  intro="Branded QR codes tend to get scanned more often. Upload your logo, match your brand colors, and download a print-ready file — free, no watermark."
  slug="qr-code-with-logo"
  defaultTab="url"
  steps={[
    'Enter your URL or content, then upload your logo under Customize — PNG, JPG, SVG, and WebP all work.',
    'Pick your brand colors. Keep strong contrast between the code color and background so scanners can read it.',
    'Download as PNG for web and social, or SVG for business cards, packaging, and large-format printing.',
  ]}
  bullets={[
    '🛡️ Error correction is automatically raised to High (30%) when you add a logo, so the code stays reliably scannable even with the center covered.',
    '🎨 The logo is sized to 22% of the code with a clean background pad — the sweet spot between visibility and scannability.',
    '🖨️ SVG export embeds your logo too, so you get one vector file ready for print shops — a feature most generators charge for.',
    '✅ No watermark ever. Many "free" generators stamp their own branding on your code or blur it behind a paywall. Yours stays yours.',
  ]}
  faqs={[
    {
      q: 'Will a logo stop my QR code from scanning?',
      a: 'Not if it is done right. QR codes include built-in error correction; at the High level, up to 30% of the code can be covered and it still scans. We size the logo well under that threshold and raise error correction automatically.',
    },
    {
      q: 'What logo formats can I upload?',
      a: 'PNG, JPG, SVG, and WebP. Square logos with transparent or white backgrounds look best. The logo never leaves your browser — it is composited locally.',
    },
    {
      q: 'Can I change the QR code colors?',
      a: 'Yes. Pick any foreground and background color. For reliable scanning, keep the code darker than the background — scanners expect dark modules on a light field.',
    },
    {
      q: 'Is the logo feature really free?',
      a: 'Yes. Logo, custom colors, high-resolution PNG, and vector SVG export are all free with no watermark. Premium is only for dynamic codes with editing and scan analytics.',
    },
    {
      q: 'Should I test the code before printing?',
      a: 'Always. Scan the preview with a couple of different phones before sending anything to print, especially if you used custom colors or a large logo.',
    },
  ]}
/>
